===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-toward.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Preposition===
'''toward''' or '''towards''' ''(mainly UK)''
# In the direction of (but not necessarily arriving at).
# In relation to (someone or something).
# For the purpose of (attaining an aim).
# Located close to; near (a time or place).

According to Associated Press style, "toward" should always be used, never "towards."

